You are working in a Next.js 15 (App Router) project: `my-finance-tracker`.

## Coding style
- Prefer TypeScript everywhere. No `any`. Keep types close to the feature folder (`src/features/...`).
- Use React Server Components by default. Mark files `"use client"` only when needed (state, effects, DOM APIs, charts).
- Keep components small and composable. Avoid giant files.
- Tailwind first. Avoid custom CSS unless it is a reusable token/theme rule.
- Use the project design tokens from `src/styles/globals.css`:
  - Prefer Tailwind/shadcn tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `border-border`, etc.) for general UI.
  - For “finance legacy style” areas, you may reference the user tokens (`--bg`, `--surface`, `--accent-ui`, etc.) but do not introduce new random colors.

## Architecture
- Feature-first structure:
  - `src/features/finance/*` holds all finance logic, store, types, selectors, UI building blocks.
  - `src/app/finance/*` contains route pages and layout only (composition + data wiring).
- State management:
  - Use Zustand stores inside feature folders (e.g. `src/features/finance/store.ts`).
  - Persist only what is needed. Prefer `zustand/middleware` `persist`.
  - Do not mutate state directly; create new objects (use `structuredClone` when convenient).

## UI conventions
- Use shadcn/ui primitives when possible (Button, DropdownMenu, Dialog, etc.).
- Dark mode must work. Theme switching uses `next-themes` and a `.dark` class.
- Keep copy/labels in Ukrainian unless the existing UI explicitly uses English.

## Data & formatting
- Dates are stored as ISO `YYYY-MM-DD`.
- Money formatting should use `uk-UA` locale and currency symbols consistent with the legacy app.
- Transfers are modeled as a pair of transactions (`income` + `expense`) linked by `transferId`, but rendered as a single row in the UI.

## Quality bar
- After edits, ensure `next lint` would pass.
- No dead code or unused imports.
- Prefer accessibility: proper buttons/labels, keyboard close for dialogs, focus handling.

